HEADWORD: Affective
<hw>Af*fec"tive</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>affectif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Tending to affect;
affecting.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Burnet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to or exciting emotion; affectional;
emotional.</def> <rj><au>Rogers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Affectively</ent>⟦br⟧
